{"type":"text","timestamp":1775849455036,"sessionID":"ses_28720996affew9EoH5UY0m3QcP","part":{"id":"prt_d78e03a38001sOp7NmErh7vIYC","messageID":"msg_d78e030310012a7vD7KkSLDhT3","sessionID":"ses_28720996affew9EoH5UY0m3QcP","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the design document for AR-010 — Router Session Management. This feature adds session management capabilities to the router, including session creation, tracking, lifecycle management, and integration with the session store.","time":{"start":1775849455035,"end":1775849455035}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849561488,"sessionID":"ses_28720996affew9EoH5UY0m3QcP","part":{"id":"prt_d78e03dbd001SiGtP30K76snxJ","messageID":"msg_d78e030310012a7vD7KkSLDhT3","sessionID":"ses_28720996affew9EoH5UY0m3QcP","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_72f0a98e18c8466aac0731b9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md","content":"# Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Session Creation**: Create a new session when a client makes the first request to a backend\n2. **Session Tracking**: Track active sessions per backend (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n3. **Session Binding**: Bind client requests to specific backend instances based on session affinity\n4. **Session Timeout**: Enforce session timeout policies (idle timeout, max duration)\n5. **Session Cleanup**: Clean up expired or abandoned sessions\n6. **Session Metrics**: Expose metrics for active sessions, session creation rate, etc.\n\n### Non-Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Performance**: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99\n2. **Scalability**: Support 10,000+ concurrent sessions\n3. **Reliability**: Session data persisted in Redis for recovery\n4. **Thread Safety**: Safe concurrent access from multiple goroutines\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── router.go                      # Main router implementation\n├── router_test.go                 # Unit tests\n├── handler.go                     # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n├── handler_test.go                # Handler tests\n├── resolver.go                    # Route resolution logic\n├── resolver_test.go               # Resolver tests\n├── health.go                      # Health check manager\n├── health_test.go                 # Health check tests\n├── config.go                      # Configuration structures\n├── types.go                       # Type definitions\n├── session/                       # NEW: Session management package\n│   ├── manager.go                 # Session manager implementation\n│   ├── manager_test.go            # Manager tests\n│   ├── session.go                 # Session data structure\n│   ├── session_test.go            # Session tests\n│   ├── store.go                   # Session storage interface\n│   ├── store_test.go              # Store tests\n│   ├── redis_store.go             # Redis-backed session store\n│   ├── redis_store_test.go        # Redis store tests\n│   ├── memory_store.go            # In-memory session store (dev/test)\n│   ├── memory_store_test.go       # Memory store tests\n│   └── config.go                  # Session configuration\n└── middleware/                    # NEW: HTTP middleware\n    ├── session_middleware.go      # Session extraction/attachment\n    ├── session_middleware_test.go # Middleware tests\n    └── auth_middleware.go         # Authentication middleware\n```\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **Session Store**: Redis (production) or in-memory (dev/test) for session persistence\n- **Clientset**: Uses generated `versioned.Clientset` for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **Informers**: Watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources\n- **Existing Router**: Extends AR-009 router with session-aware routing\n\n### High-Level Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐\n│   Client    │\n└──────┬──────┘\n       │ HTTP Request (with/without session token)\n       ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n│   Session Middleware            │\n│   - Extract session token       │\n│   - Validate session            │\n│   - Attach to context           │\n└──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n               │\n               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n│   Handler                       │\n│   - Check session affinity      │\n│   - Resolve backend             │\n└──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n               │\n               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n│   Session Manager               │\n│   - Get/Create session          │\n│   - Update last activity        │\n│   - Bind to backend             │\n└──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n               │\n               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n│   Resolver                      │\n│   - Look up route entry         │\n│   - Apply session affinity      │\n└──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n               │\n               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n│   Backend (AgentRuntime/CI)     │\n│   - Proxy request               │\n└─────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Session Lifecycle\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐\n│   Created    │ (first request or explicit creation)\n└──────┬───────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│   Active     │ (requests being processed)\n└──────┬───────┘\n       │\n       ├─ Idle Timeout ──▶ ┌──────────────┐\n       │                   │   Expired    │\n       ├─ Max Duration ──▶ └──────┬───────┘\n       │                          │\n       ▼                          ▼\n┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐\n│  Terminated  │◀─────────│  Cleanup     │\n└──────────────┘  (delete) └──────────────┘\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Session\n\n```go\ntype Session struct {\n    // Unique session identifier\n    ID string `json:\"id\"`\n    \n    // Namespace of the backend resource\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n    \n    // Backend kind: \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    Kind string `json:\"kind\"`\n    \n    // Name of the backend resource\n    BackendName string `json:\"backendName\"`\n    \n    // Backend URL for routing\n    BackendURL string `json:\"backendURL\"`\n    \n    // User identifier (from auth token or request header)\n    UserID string `json:\"userId\"`\n    \n    // Session creation time\n    CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    \n    // Last activity timestamp\n    LastActivityAt time.Time `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n    \n    // Session expiration time (CreatedAt + MaxDuration)\n    ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    \n    // Session state\n    State SessionState `json:\"state\"`\n    \n    // Metadata for extensibility\n    Metadata map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // Lock for concurrent access\n    mu sync.RWMutex\n}\n\ntype SessionState string\n\nconst (\n    SessionStateActive     SessionState = \"Active\"\n    SessionStateIdle       SessionState = \"Idle\"\n    SessionStateExpired    SessionState = \"Expired\"\n    SessionStateTerminated SessionState = \"Terminated\"\n)\n```\n\n### SessionConfig\n\n```go\ntype SessionConfig struct {\n    // Enable session management\n    Enabled bool\n    \n    // Session cookie name\n    CookieName string\n    \n    // Session cookie domain (optional)\n    CookieDomain string\n    \n    // Session cookie path\n    CookiePath string\n    \n    // Session cookie secure flag\n    CookieSecure bool\n    \n    // Session cookie HTTP-only flag\n    CookieHTTPOnly bool\n    \n    // Session cookie SameSite policy\n    CookieSameSite http.SameSite\n    \n    // Session token header name\n    TokenHeader string\n    \n    // Maximum session duration\n    MaxDuration time.Duration\n    \n    // Idle session timeout\n    IdleTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // Session cleanup interval\n    CleanupInterval time.Duration\n    \n    // Store type: \"redis\" or \"memory\"\n    StoreType string\n    \n    // Redis configuration\n    Redis RedisSessionConfig\n}\n\ntype RedisSessionConfig struct {\n    // Redis address\n    Addr string\n    \n    // Redis password\n    Password string\n    \n    // Redis database number\n    DB int\n    \n    // Session key prefix\n    KeyPrefix string\n    \n    // Connection pool size\n    PoolSize int\n    \n    // Connection timeout\n    DialTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // Read timeout\n    ReadTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // Write timeout\n    WriteTimeout time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### SessionManager\n\n```go\ntype SessionManager struct {\n    config    *SessionConfig\n    store     SessionStore\n    metrics   *SessionMetrics\n    stopCh    chan struct{}\n    wg        sync.WaitGroup\n    mu        sync.RWMutex\n}\n\ntype SessionStore interface {\n    // Get retrieves a session by ID\n    Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n    \n    // Set stores or updates a session\n    Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n    \n    // Delete removes a session\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    \n    // List returns sessions matching namespace and kind\n    List(ctx context.Context, namespace, kind string) ([]*Session, error)\n    \n    // ListByUser returns sessions for a specific user\n    ListByUser(ctx context.Context, userID string) ([]*Session, error)\n    \n    // Close closes the store connection\n    Close() error\n}\n\ntype SessionMetrics struct {\n    ActiveSessions   prometheus.Gauge\n    SessionsCreated  prometheus.Counter\n    SessionsExpired  prometheus.Counter\n    SessionsTerminated prometheus.Counter\n    SessionDuration  prometheus.Histogram\n    StoreLatency     prometheus.Histogram\n}\n```\n\n### SessionMiddleware\n\n```go\ntype SessionMiddleware struct {\n    manager *SessionManager\n    config  *SessionConfig\n}\n\n// ExtractSession extracts session from request\nfunc (m *SessionMiddleware) ExtractSession(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n\n// AttachSession attaches session to response\nfunc (m *SessionMiddleware) AttachSession(w http.ResponseWriter, session *Session)\n\n// WithSession wraps handler with session context\nfunc (m *SessionMiddleware) WithSession(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Session Token Format\n\n**Cookie-based (default):**\n```\nSet-Cookie: agentcube_session=<session-id>; Path=/; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict\n```\n\n**Header-based (alternative):**\n```\nX-AgentCube-Session: <session-id>\n```\n\n**JWT Payload (optional, for auth integration):**\n```json\n{\n  \"sub\": \"user-123\",\n  \"sid\": \"session-abc\",\n  \"nss\": \"default\",\n  \"bk\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n  \"bkn\": \"my-runtime\",\n  \"iat\": 1699000000,\n  \"exp\": 1699086400\n}\n```\n\n### Session Endpoints\n\nThe router exposes management endpoints for session operations:\n\n```\nGET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n       - List all active sessions\n       - Query params: namespace, kind, userId\n\nGET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n       - Get session details\n\nDELETE /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n       - Terminate a session\n\nPOST   /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n       - Create a new session (explicit)\n       - Body: { \"namespace\", \"kind\", \"backendName\", \"userId\" }\n```\n\n### Session Management Interface\n\n```go\ntype SessionManagerInterface interface {\n    // CreateSession creates a new session\n    CreateSession(ctx context.Context, req *CreateSessionRequest) (*Session, error)\n    \n    // GetSession retrieves a session by ID\n    GetSession(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n    \n    // UpdateSession updates session metadata\n    UpdateSession(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n    \n    // DeleteSession terminates and removes a session\n    DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    \n    // ListSessions returns sessions matching filters\n    ListSessions(ctx context.Context, filters *SessionFilters) ([]*Session, error)\n    \n    // CleanupExpiredSessions removes expired sessions\n    CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n    \n    // Start starts the session manager background tasks\n    Start(ctx context.Context) error\n    \n    // Shutdown gracefully stops the session manager\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n\ntype CreateSessionRequest struct {\n    Namespace   string\n    Kind        string\n    BackendName string\n    BackendURL  string\n    UserID      string\n    Metadata    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype SessionFilters struct {\n    Namespace string\n    Kind      string\n    UserID    string\n    State     SessionState\n}\n```\n\n### Resolve with Session Affinity\n\n**Modified Resolve Operation:**\n\n```go\n// ResolveWithSession resolves route considering session affinity\nfunc (r *Resolver) ResolveWithSession(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    req *http.Request,\n    session *Session,\n) (*RouteEntry, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. If session exists and is bound to a backend → return that backend\n2. If session exists but backend is unhealthy → reassign to healthy backend\n3. If no session → select backend using load balancing strategy\n4. Update session's LastActivityAt timestamp\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    // Session errors\n    ErrSessionNotFound      = errors.New(\"session not found\")\n    ErrSessionExpired       = errors.New(\"session has expired\")\n    ErrSessionTerminated    = errors.New(\"session was terminated\")\n    ErrSessionCreateFailed  = errors.New(\"failed to create session\")\n    ErrSessionStoreError    = errors.New(\"session store error\")\n    \n    // Session affinity errors\n    ErrBackendUnavailable   = errors.New(\"backend unavailable for session\")\n    ErrAffinityBroken       = errors.New(\"session affinity cannot be maintained\")\n    \n    // Configuration errors\n    ErrInvalidSessionConfig = errors.New(\"invalid session configuration\")\n    ErrRedisConnectionFailed = errors.New(\"failed to connect to redis\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```go\ntype SessionErrorResponse struct {\n    Error       string            `json:\"error\"`\n    Code        string            `json:\"code\"`\n    SessionID   string            `json:\"sessionId,omitempty\"`\n    Details     map[string]string `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n    Timestamp   string            `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n\n// Error codes\nconst (\n    ErrCodeSessionNotFound      = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrCodeSessionExpired       = \"SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n    ErrCodeSessionTerminated    = \"SESSION_TERMINATED\"\n    ErrCodeBackendUnavailable   = \"BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE\"\n    ErrCodeAffinityBroken       = \"AFFINITY_BROKEN\"\n)\n```\n\n### Session Recovery Strategy\n\n| Scenario | Action |\n|----------|--------|\n| Session not found | Create new session, return 201 |\n| Session expired | Clean up, create new session |\n| Backend unhealthy | Reassign to healthy backend (if allowed) |\n| Redis connection lost | Fall back to memory store (if configured) |\n| Session store error | Log error, continue with degraded mode |\n\n### Graceful Degradation\n\n```go\ntype FallbackStrategy string\n\nconst (\n    FallbackMemory FallbackStrategy = \"memory\" // Use in-memory store\n    FallbackDirect FallbackStrategy = \"direct\" // Direct routing without sessions\n    FallbackReject FallbackStrategy = \"reject\" // Reject requests\n)\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `session/manager_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestSessionManager_CreateSession(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_GetSession(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_DeleteSession(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_ListSessions(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_CleanupExpiredSessions(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_SessionAffinity(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File**: `session/session_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestSession_IsExpired(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSession_IsIdle(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSession_UpdateActivity(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSession_MarshalJSON(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSession_ThreadSafety(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File**: `session/redis_store_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestRedisStore_GetSet(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRedisStore_Delete(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRedisStore_List(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRedisStore_ListByUser(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRedisStore_ConnectionFailure(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRedisStore_KeyExpiration(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File**: `session/memory_store_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestMemoryStore_BasicOperations(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestMemoryStore_ListFiltering(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestMemoryStore_MemoryLimit(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File**: `middleware/session_middleware_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Cookie(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Header(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionMiddleware_AttachSession(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_Success(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_InvalidToken(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestSession(id, namespace, backendName, userID string) *Session {\n    return &Session{\n        ID:             id,\n        Namespace:      namespace,\n        Kind:           \"AgentRuntime\",\n        BackendName:    backendName,\n        BackendURL:     \"http://backend:8080\",\n        UserID:         userID,\n        CreatedAt:      time.Now(),\n        LastActivityAt: time.Now(),\n        ExpiresAt:      time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n        State:          SessionStateActive,\n    }\n}\n\nfunc newTestSessionConfig() *SessionConfig {\n    return &SessionConfig{\n        Enabled:         true,\n        CookieName:      \"agentcube_session\",\n        TokenHeader:     \"X-AgentCube-Session\",\n        MaxDuration:     8 * time.Hour,\n        IdleTimeout:     15 * time.Minute,\n        CleanupInterval: 1 * time.Minute,\n        StoreType:       \"memory\",\n    }\n}\n\nfunc newTestRedisConfig(addr, password string) *RedisSessionConfig {\n    return &RedisSessionConfig{\n        Addr:         addr,\n        Password:     password,\n        DB:           0,\n        KeyPrefix:    \"agentcube:session:\",\n        PoolSize:     10,\n        DialTimeout:  5 * time.Second,\n        ReadTimeout:  3 * time.Second,\n        WriteTimeout: 3 * time.Second,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Mock Setup\n\n```go\n// Mock session store for testing\ntype MockSessionStore struct {\n    sessions sync.Map\n    mu       sync.Mutex\n}\n\nfunc (m *MockSessionStore) Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error) {\n    if v, ok := m.sessions.Load(id); ok {\n        return v.(*Session), nil\n    }\n    return nil, ErrSessionNotFound\n}\n\nfunc (m *MockSessionStore) Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error {\n    m.sessions.Store(session.ID, session)\n    return nil\n}\n\n// Mock Redis server for integration tests\nfunc newMockRedisServer() *miniredis.Miniredis {\n    mr, _ := miniredis.Run()\n    return mr\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `session/session_integration_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test scenarios (requires Redis):\nfunc TestSessionManager_RedisPersistence(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_SessionExpiration(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_ConcurrentSessionAccess(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_CleanupRoutine(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestSessionManager_Failover(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n### Performance Tests\n\n```go\nfunc BenchmarkSessionManager_CreateSession(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkSessionManager_GetSession(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkSessionStore_Redis(b *testing.B)\nfunc BenchmarkSessionStore_Memory(b *testing.B)\n```\n\n### Coverage Requirements\n\n- Session manager: 100%\n- Session store implementations: 100%\n- Middleware: 100%\n- Error handling paths: 100%\n- Overall: ≥85%\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Session ID Generation\n\n```go\nfunc GenerateSessionID() string {\n    // Format: sess_<timestamp>_<random>\n    // Example: sess_1699000000_abc123def456\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"sess_%d_%s\", \n        time.Now().UnixNano(),\n        base64.RawURLEncoding.EncodeToString(randomBytes(16)),\n    )\n}\n```\n\n### Redis Key Schema\n\n```\n# Session data (with TTL)\nagentcube:session:{session-id} = JSON(session)\n\n# User session index (Set)\nagentcube:user:{user-id}:sessions = {session-id-1, session-id-2, ...}\n\n# Backend session index (Set)\nagentcube:backend:{namespace}:{kind}:{name}:sessions = {session-id-1, ...}\n\n# Active sessions counter\nagentcube:stats:active_sessions = {count}\n```\n\n### Session Cleanup Strategy\n\n```go\n// Background cleanup routine\nfunc (m *SessionManager) cleanupLoop(ctx context.Context) {\n    ticker := time.NewTicker(m.config.CleanupInterval)\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            expired, err := m.CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx)\n            if err != nil {\n                m.metrics.ErrorsTotal.Inc()\n            }\n            m.metrics.SessionsExpired.Add(float64(expired))\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Session Affinity Algorithm\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Resolver) resolveWithAffinity(\n    session *Session,\n    availableBackends []*RouteEntry,\n) (*RouteEntry, error) {\n    // Priority 1: Session's current backend (if healthy)\n    if session != nil {\n        for _, backend := range availableBackends {\n            if backend.Name == session.BackendName && backend.Health.Healthy {\n                return backend, nil\n            }\n        }\n        // Current backend unhealthy - need to reassign\n    }\n    \n    // Priority 2: Least loaded healthy backend\n    return selectLeastLoaded(availableBackends), nil\n}\n```\n\n### Connection Pool Configuration\n\n```go\nfunc NewRedisPool(config *RedisSessionConfig) *redis.Client {\n    return redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n        Addr:         config.Addr,\n        Password:     config.Password,\n        DB:           config.DB,\n        PoolSize:     config.PoolSize,\n        MinIdleConns: config.PoolSize / 2,\n        MaxConnAge:   24 * time.Hour,\n        DialTimeout:  config.DialTimeout,\n        ReadTimeout:  config.ReadTimeout,\n        WriteTimeout: config.WriteTimeout,\n        OnConnect: func(ctx context.Context, cn *redis.Conn) error {\n            log.Printf(\"Redis connection established: %v\", cn)\n            return nil\n        },\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### Graceful Shutdown\n\n```go\nfunc (m *SessionManager) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n    // 1. Stop cleanup loop\n    close(m.stopCh)\n    \n    // 2. Wait for background tasks\n    done := make(chan struct{})\n    go func() {\n        m.wg.Wait()\n        close(done)\n    }()\n    \n    select {\n    case <-done:\n        // Cleanup completed\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        return ctx.Err()\n    case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n        return errors.New(\"shutdown timeout\")\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Persist in-memory sessions (if using memory store)\n    if ms, ok := m.store.(*MemoryStore); ok {\n        if err := ms.Persist(ctx); err != nil {\n            log.Printf(\"Failed to persist sessions: %v\", err)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 4. Close store connection\n    return m.store.Close()\n}\n```\n\n### Metrics Exposure\n\n```go\n// Prometheus metrics\nfunc (m *SessionManager) RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) {\n    m.metrics.ActiveSessions = prometheus.NewGauge(prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n        Name: \"agentcube_router_active_sessions\",\n        Help: \"Number of active sessions\",\n    })\n    \n    m.metrics.SessionsCreated = prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n        Name: \"agentcube_router_sessions_created_total\",\n        Help: \"Total number of sessions created\",\n    })\n    \n    m.metrics.SessionDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n        Name:    \"agentcube_router_session_duration_seconds\",\n        Help:    \"Session duration in seconds\",\n        Buckets: prometheus.ExponentialBuckets(60, 2, 10),\n    })\n    \n    reg.MustRegister(\n        m.metrics.ActiveSessions,\n        m.metrics.SessionsCreated,\n        m.metrics.SessionsExpired,\n        m.metrics.SessionsTerminated,\n        m.metrics.SessionDuration,\n        m.metrics.StoreLatency,\n    )\n}\n```\n\n### Configuration Example\n\n```yaml\n# Helm values.yaml\nrouter:\n  session:\n    enabled: true\n    cookieName: agentcube_session\n    maxDuration: 8h\n    idleTimeout: 15m\n    cleanupInterval: 1m\n    store:\n      type: redis\n      redis:\n        addr: redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\n        password: \"\"\n        db: 0\n        keyPrefix: \"agentcube:session:\"\n        poolSize: 10\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n```bash\nAGENTCUBE_SESSION_ENABLED=true\nAGENTCUBE_SESSION_COOKIE_NAME=agentcube_session\nAGENTCUBE_SESSION_MAX_DURATION=8h\nAGENTCUBE_SESSION_IDLE_TIMEOUT=15m\nAGENTCUBE_SESSION_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=1m\nAGENTCUBE_SESSION_STORE_TYPE=redis\nAGENTCUBE_REDIS_ADDR=redis:6379\nAGENTCUBE_REDIS_PASSWORD=\nAGENTCUBE_REDIS_DB=0\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md","time":{"start":1775849561474,"end":1775849561484}}}}
